nistrators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: British individuals, Healers, Males,     and 3 more    Poke family   St Mungo's employees   Wizards             English     Français   Polski               Rutherford Poke              View source                         History                         Talk (0)                                   Rutherford Poke   Biographical information  Born Prior to 2010   Nationality British[1]   Title(s) Healer[1]    Physical information  Species Human[1]   Gender Male[1]    Relationship information  Family members Royden Poke (possibly)    Affiliation  Occupation Healer at and spokeperson for St Mungo's Hospital for Magical Maladies and Injuries[1]   Loyalty St Mungo's Hospital for Magical Maladies and Injuries[1]   [Source]    "It's two Sickles a scoop, people, so stop being cheap, stop throwing powdered Runespoor fangs on the fire and stop blowing yourselves out of the chimney! If one more wizard comes in here with a burned backside, I swear I won't treat him. It's two Sickles a scoop!" — Statement by Poke on the use of homemade Floo Powder substitutes[src]  Rutherford Poke was a Healer at and a spokesperson for St Mungo's Hospital for Magical Maladies and Injuries.[1]  Contents  1 Biography 2 Magical abilities and skills 3 Appearances 4 Notes and references   Biography In 2010, he lamented the incidence of injuries caused by people attempting to use homemade substitutes for Floo Powder, reminding people that the authentic article only cost two Sickles per scoop, and swearing he would refuse to treat the next wizard who came into St Mungo's with a burned bottom.[1]  Magical abilities and skills Healing magic: As a professional Healer, Rutherhood would have been highly adept and accomplished with medical magic, such as with healing spells, potions and other magical remedies.[1] Appearances Pottermore (First mentioned) Wizarding World (Mentioned only) Notes and references   ↑ 1.0 1.1 1.2 1.3 1.4 1.5